[2] Cholera, water supply - Ukraine (Zaporizhzhya)
Date: Tue 17 Aug 2010
Source: Ukraine Radio [edited]
<http://www.nrcu.gov.ua/index.php?id=148&listid=125950>


Cholera bacteria were found in Dnieper [River] water near
Zaporizhzhya. As reported by the regional sanitary epidemiological
station, swimming is prohibited on the central beaches near the
Khortytsya island and on the beaches located on the area from the
Dniprohes hydroelectric power station to the lower limits of the city.

Cholera bacteria were found during monitoring of water in the Dnieper
near the Embankment on the central beach and purification
installations of water supply system. Epidemiologists warn that
infection can cause serious gastrointestinal diseases. Therefore, to
swim in such water and the more so to drink the Dnieper is dangerous.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[No clinical cases are reported but finding _Vibrio cholerae_ in the
water suggests that human infection may well have occurred. - Mod.LL]

[Maps of Ukraine are available at
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/ukraine.pdf> and
<http://healthmap.org/r/02SX>. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

