[4] Cholera - Pakistan (Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa)
Date: Tue 17 Aug 2010
Source: Arirang (South Korea) [edited]
<http://www.arirang.co.kr/News/News_View.asp?nseq=105969&code=Ne2&category=2>


The WHO has asked Pakistan to investigate a reported case of cholera
in the northwest Swat Valley [Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa/Northwest Frontier
Province] amid fears that an epidemic could break out in its flood-hit regions.

The international health body says cholera, which is endemic in the
flood-affected country has a high chance of spreading rapidly after
floods and other disasters. WHO spokesman Paul Garwood said
international health rules require Pakistan to probe into the case
and report back to the organization.

If an epidemic were to occur the WHO says close to 140 000 cases of
cholera could sweep the country over the next 3 months.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This posting does not repudiate the reported case, but rather
suggest more investigation of the case is needed. - Mod.LL]

